quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,82,"They said: "
  23,83,""
  23,84,"Say: "
  24,64,"Certainly, to Allâh belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth. Surely, He knows your condition and (He knows) the Day when they will be brought back to Him, then He will inform them of what they did. And Allâh is All-Knower of everything."
  25,28,""
  25,29,""
  25,30,"And the Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) will say: "
  26,1,"Tâ-Sîn-Mîm."
  26,2,"These are the Verses of the manifest Book [(this Qur’ân), which was promised by Allâh in the Taurât (Torah) and the Injeel (Gospel), makes things clear]."
  26,3,"It may be that you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) are going to kill yourself with grief, that they do not become believers [in your Risalah (Messengership) i.e. in your Message of Islâmic Monotheism].{1}",1:[{26:3} See the footnote of (Verse 3:85).]
